SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 959
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Dr. Carroll Van West for
his service to the people of the State of
Tennessee.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly recognize those
devoted Tennesseans who endeavor to preserve and further the appreciation of the history of
this State; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Carroll Van West has tirelessly promoted the love of history and an
appreciation for historic preservation across the State of Tennessee and beyond for over forty
years; and
WHEREAS, Dr. West has been recognized by national, state, and local organizations for
his never-failing contributions to historic preservation; and
WHEREAS, Dr. West obtained his undergraduate degree from Middle Tennessee State
University in 1977, his master's degree from the University of Tennessee in 1978, and his Ph.D.
from the College of William and Mary in 1982; and
WHEREAS, in 1985, Dr. West was selected to join the Center for Historic Preservation
at Middle Tennessee State University and thereafter, in 2002, became the director of the
Center, a position he has held since then; and
WHEREAS, as director of the Center for Historic Preservation, Dr. West has directed the
Tennessee Civil War National Heritage Area, served as editor-in-chief of the Tennessee
Encyclopedia of History and Culture, and directed and consulted with organizations across the
State of Tennessee and a number of other states to save important historic sites, develop
historic trails, and assist with expanding National Register properties; and
