WHEREAS, since 1984, Dr. West has served at MTSU as a professor of history, in
which position he has inspired legions of students to pursue career paths as history teachers,
historic preservationists, and history consultants; and
WHEREAS, Dr. West is well known as an author and editor; in addition to the
Tennessee Encyclopedia of History and Culture, his many other books and publications include
the Tennessee Historical Quarterly; Nashville Architecture: A Guide to the City; A History of the
Arts in Tennessee; Trial and Triumph: Readings in Tennessee's African American Past;
Tennessee's New Deal Landscape; Tennessee History: The Land, The People, and The
Culture; and Tennessee's Historic Landscapes; and
WHEREAS, in 2013, Dr. West was named the Tennessee State Historian; and
WHEREAS, throughout his career, Dr. West has built a legacy of ensuring that historic
preservation is a part of Tennessee's culture and ethic for generations to come; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Dr. Carroll Van West for
more than forty years of dedicated service to the people of the State of Tennessee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
